## Section 9: Button Component

### 9.1 Component Overview

**Description**: A versatile button component with 5 variants, 4 sizes, loading states, and icon support. Used for all CTAs, form submissions, and interactive actions.

**Location**: `src/components/ui/Button.tsx`

**When to Use**:
- ✅ Actions that trigger immediate changes (submit forms, trigger APIs)
- ✅ Primary, secondary, and destructive actions
- ✅ Navigation that performs an action first (save and continue)

**When NOT to Use**:
- ❌ Pure navigation without actions → Use `<Link>` or `<a>`
- ❌ Text that needs to be copyable → Use styled text
- ❌ Toggle switches → Use `<Switch>` component

---

### 9.2 TypeScript Interface

```typescript
interface ButtonProps extends React.ButtonHTMLAttributes<HTMLButtonElement> {
  /** Visual style variant */
  variant?: 'primary' | 'secondary' | 'outline' | 'ghost' | 'danger';

  /** Size of the button */
  size?: 'sm' | 'md' | 'lg' | 'xl';

  /** Show loading spinner, disables button */
  isLoading?: boolean;

  /** Icon to display before text */
  leftIcon?: React.ReactNode;

  /** Icon to display after text */
  rightIcon?: React.ReactNode;

  /** Stretch button to full container width */
  fullWidth?: boolean;

  /** All standard HTML button attributes */
  disabled?: boolean;
  type?: 'button' | 'submit' | 'reset';
  onClick?: React.MouseEventHandler<HTMLButtonElement>;
  className?: string;
  children: React.ReactNode;
}
```

---

### 9.3 All Variants (5 Variants)

#### Variant: Primary

**Visual Specs**:
- Background: Blue gradient `from-blue-600 to-blue-500`
- Text: White
- Shadow: `shadow-lg` with blue glow on hover
- Focus Ring: `focus:ring-blue-400/50`

**CSS Classes**:
```css
bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-600 to-blue-500 text-white
hover:from-blue-700 hover:to-blue-600
focus:ring-blue-400/50
shadow-lg hover:shadow-xl hover:shadow-blue-500/25
```

**When to Use**:
- ✅ **THE most important action on the page**
- ✅ Form submissions
- ✅ Payment/checkout buttons
- ✅ "Continue", "Submit", "Complete" actions

**CRITICAL RULE**: Maximum 1 primary button per visible screen area

**Code Example**:
```tsx
import Button from '@/components/ui/Button';
import { CreditCard } from 'lucide-react';

<Button
  variant="primary"
  size="lg"
  leftIcon={<CreditCard />}
  onClick={handlePayment}
>
  Pay ₹{amount.toLocaleString('en-IN')}
</Button>
```

**Anti-Patterns**:
- ❌ Multiple primary buttons on same screen
- ❌ Primary button for "Cancel" or "Back"
- ❌ Primary button hidden below fold

---

#### Variant: Secondary

**Visual Specs**:
- Background: Teal gradient `from-teal-600 to-teal-500`
- Text: White
- Shadow: `shadow-lg` with teal glow on hover
- Focus Ring: `focus:ring-teal-400/50`

**When to Use**:
- ✅ Alternative important actions
- ✅ "Save Draft", "Schedule", "Export"
- ✅ Actions that support the primary flow
- ✅ Can have 2-3 secondary buttons on screen

**Code Example**:
```tsx
<Button
  variant="secondary"
  size="md"
  onClick={handleSaveDraft}
>
  Save Draft
</Button>
```

---

#### Variant: Outline

**Visual Specs**:
- Background: Transparent with glass effect (`backdrop-blur-sm`)
- Border: `border-2 border-white/30` → `hover:border-white/50`
- Text: White
- Hover: `hover:bg-white/10`

**When to Use**:
- ✅ Cancel actions
- ✅ Alternative paths
- ✅ "Skip", "Back", "Cancel"
- ✅ Secondary navigation

**Code Example**:
```tsx
<Button
  variant="outline"
  size="md"
  onClick={handleCancel}
>
  Cancel
</Button>
```

---

#### Variant: Ghost

**Visual Specs**:
- Background: Transparent
- Text: `text-white/80` → `hover:text-white`
- Hover: `hover:bg-white/10`
- No border

**When to Use**:
- ✅ Subtle actions
- ✅ Inline actions within text
- ✅ Icon-only buttons
- ✅ Menu items

**Code Example**:
```tsx
<Button
  variant="ghost"
  size="sm"
  leftIcon={<Download />}
>
  Download Receipt
</Button>
```

---

#### Variant: Danger

**Visual Specs**:
- Background: Red gradient `from-red-600 to-red-500`
- Text: White
- Shadow: `shadow-lg` with red glow on hover
- Focus Ring: `focus:ring-red-400/50`

**When to Use**:
- ✅ Destructive actions
- ✅ "Delete", "Remove", "Cancel Subscription"
- ✅ Actions that cannot be easily undone

**CRITICAL RULE**: Always show confirmation modal before destructive action

**Code Example**:
```tsx
const [showConfirm, setShowConfirm] = useState(false);

<>
  <Button
    variant="danger"
    size="md"
    onClick={() => setShowConfirm(true)}
  >
    Delete Account
  </Button>

  {showConfirm && (
    <ConfirmModal
      title="Delete Account"
      message="This action cannot be undone. Are you sure?"
      confirmText="Yes, Delete"
      onConfirm={handleDelete}
      onCancel={() => setShowConfirm(false)}
    />
  )}
</>
```

---

### 9.4 All Sizes (4 Sizes)

| Size | Height | Padding | Font Size | Icon Size | Gap | Use Case |
|------|--------|---------|-----------|-----------|-----|----------|
| **sm** | ~38px | px-4 py-2 | text-sm (14px) | 16px | gap-2 | Compact UIs, tables, inline actions |
| **md** | ~48px | px-6 py-3 | text-base (16px) | 20px | gap-2 | **Standard buttons (DEFAULT)** |
| **lg** | ~56px | px-8 py-4 | text-lg (18px) | 24px | gap-3 | Primary CTAs, payment buttons |
| **xl** | ~56px | px-8 py-4 | text-xl (20px) | 28px | gap-3 | Hero buttons, landing pages |

**Code Examples**:
```tsx
// Small button for table actions
<Button variant="ghost" size="sm" leftIcon={<Edit />}>
  Edit
</Button>

// Medium button (default) for forms
<Button variant="primary" size="md">
  Submit Form
</Button>

// Large button for payment
<Button variant="primary" size="lg" fullWidth>
  Complete Payment
</Button>

// Extra large for hero section
<Button variant="primary" size="xl" rightIcon={<ArrowRight />}>
  Get Started
</Button>
```

---

### 9.5 All States (8 States)

#### State: Default
- Normal resting state
- Full color, no opacity reduction

#### State: Hover
- Gradient shifts to darker shades
- Shadow increases `shadow-lg` → `shadow-xl`
- Glow effect appears (`shadow-blue-500/25`)

#### State: Active (Pressed)
- Slight scale reduction (handled by browser)
- Darker gradient maintained

#### State: Focus
- 2px focus ring with color matching variant
- `focus:ring-2 focus:ring-{color}-400/50`
- `focus:ring-offset-2` for contrast

#### State: Disabled
- Opacity: 50% (`disabled:opacity-50`)
- Cursor: `cursor-not-allowed`
- No hover effects
- Cannot be clicked

**Code**:
```tsx
<Button variant="primary" disabled>
  Disabled Button
</Button>
```

#### State: Loading
- Spinner replaces leftIcon
- Button disabled automatically
- Text remains visible
- Spinner animates with `animate-spin`

**Code**:
```tsx
const [loading, setLoading] = useState(false);

<Button
  variant="primary"
  isLoading={loading}
  onClick={async () => {
    setLoading(true);
    await processPayment();
    setLoading(false);
  }}
>
  Process Payment
</Button>
```

#### State: Success (Temporary)
- Not built-in, implement with state change
- Show checkmark icon briefly
- Change to success variant

**Code**:
```tsx
const [status, setStatus] = useState<'idle' | 'loading' | 'success'>('idle');

<Button
  variant={status === 'success' ? 'secondary' : 'primary'}
  isLoading={status === 'loading'}
  leftIcon={status === 'success' ? <CheckCircle /> : undefined}
  onClick={async () => {
    setStatus('loading');
    await saveData();
    setStatus('success');
    setTimeout(() => setStatus('idle'), 2000);
  }}
>
  {status === 'success' ? 'Saved!' : 'Save Changes'}
</Button>
```

#### State: Error (Temporary)
- Show error icon briefly
- Change button to danger variant

---

### 9.6 Complete Code Examples

#### Example 1: Payment Button with Amount

```tsx
import Button from '@/components/ui/Button';
import { CreditCard } from 'lucide-react';
import { useState } from 'react';
import { toast } from '@/components/ui/Toast';

function CheckoutButton({ amount }: { amount: number }) {
  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(false);

  const handlePayment = async () => {
    setLoading(true);
    try {
      const response = await fetch('/api/payments/process', {
        method: 'POST',
        headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
        body: JSON.stringify({ amount }),
      });

      if (response.ok) {
        toast.show({
          type: 'success',
          title: 'Payment Successful!',
          message: `₹${amount.toLocaleString('en-IN')} has been processed.`,
        });
      } else {
        throw new Error('Payment failed');
      }
    } catch (error) {
      toast.show({
        type: 'error',
        title: 'Payment Failed',
        message: 'Please try again or contact support.',
      });
    } finally {
      setLoading(false);
    }
  };

  return (
    <Button
      variant="primary"
      size="lg"
      fullWidth
      isLoading={loading}
      leftIcon={<CreditCard className="w-5 h-5" />}
      onClick={handlePayment}
    >
      Pay ₹{amount.toLocaleString('en-IN')}
    </Button>
  );
}
```

---

#### Example 2: Danger Button with Confirmation Modal

```tsx
