---

### 9.7 Accessibility Checklist

- ✅ **Semantic HTML**: Uses `<button>` element
- ✅ **Keyboard Navigation**: Responds to Enter and Space keys (native)
- ✅ **Focus Indicators**: 2px focus ring with appropriate color
- ✅ **Disabled State**: `disabled` attribute prevents interaction
- ✅ **ARIA Label**: Use `aria-label` for icon-only buttons
- ✅ **Loading State**: Button is disabled during loading
- ✅ **Color Contrast**: All variants meet WCAG AA (white text on colored bg)
- ✅ **Touch Target**: Minimum 44px height (met by md size and above)

**Accessibility Code Example**:
```tsx
// Icon-only button with aria-label
<Button
  variant="ghost"
  size="sm"
  onClick={handleEdit}
  aria-label="Edit transaction"
>
  <Edit className="w-4 h-4" />
</Button>

// Button with loading state and screen reader text
<Button
  variant="primary"
  isLoading={loading}
  aria-busy={loading}
  aria-label={loading ? 'Processing payment' : 'Pay now'}
>
  {loading ? 'Processing...' : 'Pay Now'}
</Button>
```

---

### 9.8 Design Specifications

**Spacing**:
- Padding: Consistent with size scale (sm: px-4 py-2, md: px-6 py-3, lg: px-8 py-4)
- Gap between icon and text: gap-2 (8px) for sm/md, gap-3 (12px) for lg/xl
- Min-width: None (content-based)
- Full-width option: `w-full` class

**Typography**:
- Font Family: Inter (body font)
- Font Weight: `font-medium` (500)
- Font Sizes: Match size prop (sm: 14px, md: 16px, lg: 18px, xl: 20px)
- Line Height: Normal (1.5)
- Text Transform: None

**Colors**:
- Primary: Blue gradient #2563eb → #3b82f6
- Secondary: Teal gradient #0d9488 → #14b8a6
- Danger: Red gradient #dc2626 → #ef4444
- Outline/Ghost: White with transparency

**Effects**:
- Border Radius: `rounded-xl` (12px) for all sizes
- Shadow: `shadow-lg` default, `shadow-xl` on hover
- Glow: Colored shadow matching variant (e.g., `shadow-blue-500/25`)
- Transition: `transition-all duration-200`
- Backdrop Blur: `backdrop-blur-sm` for outline/ghost variants

---

### 9.9 Composition Breakdown (Atomic Design)

```
Button Molecule
├── Color Atoms
│   ├── Primary-600 (bg gradient start)
│   ├── Primary-500 (bg gradient end)
│   ├── White (text color)
│   └── Primary-400/50 (focus ring)
├── Spacing Atoms
│   ├── px-6 (horizontal padding)
│   ├── py-3 (vertical padding)
│   └── gap-2 (icon-text gap)
├── Typography Atoms
│   ├── text-base (font size)
│   ├── font-medium (font weight)
│   └── font-body (font family: Inter)
├── Border Radius Atom
│   └── rounded-xl (12px)
├── Shadow Atoms
│   ├── shadow-lg (default)
│   └── shadow-xl (hover)
├── Icon Atom (optional)
│   └── lucide-react icon component
├── Loading Spinner Atom (conditional)
│   └── SVG with animate-spin
└── Transition Atoms
    ├── transition-all
    └── duration-200
```

---

### 9.10 Decision Tree

```
Which button variant should I use?

├─ Is this the MOST important action on the page?
│  └─ YES → variant="primary" (MAX 1 per visible area)
│     └─ Use size="lg" for payment/checkout
│
├─ Is this a destructive/dangerous action?
│  └─ YES → variant="danger"
│     └─ ALWAYS show confirmation modal
│
├─ Is this an alternative/secondary important action?
│  └─ YES → variant="secondary"
│     └─ Can have 2-3 on same page
│
├─ Is this a cancel/back/dismiss action?
│  └─ YES → variant="outline" or "ghost"
│     └─ Use "outline" if needs more emphasis
│     └─ Use "ghost" for subtle actions
│
└─ Is this a pure navigation action (no processing)?
   └─ YES → Use <Link> component instead, not Button
```

---

### 9.11 Anti-Patterns (What NOT to Do)

❌ **Multiple Primary Buttons**
```tsx
// WRONG: Two primary buttons competing for attention
<div>
  <Button variant="primary">Save Draft</Button>
  <Button variant="primary">Submit</Button>
</div>

// CORRECT: One primary, one secondary
<div>
  <Button variant="secondary">Save Draft</Button>
  <Button variant="primary">Submit</Button>
</div>
```

❌ **Danger Button Without Confirmation**
```tsx
// WRONG: Direct deletion without confirmation
<Button variant="danger" onClick={deleteAccount}>
  Delete Account
</Button>

// CORRECT: Show confirmation modal first
<Button variant="danger" onClick={() => setShowConfirm(true)}>
  Delete Account
</Button>
```

❌ **Icon-Only Button Without aria-label**
```tsx
// WRONG: No accessible name
<Button variant="ghost">
  <Edit />
</Button>

// CORRECT: Includes aria-label
<Button variant="ghost" aria-label="Edit transaction">
  <Edit />
</Button>
```

❌ **Using Button for Pure Navigation**
```tsx
// WRONG: Button for navigation
<Button variant="primary" onClick={() => navigate('/dashboard')}>
  Go to Dashboard
</Button>

// CORRECT: Use Link component
<Link to="/dashboard" className="btn-primary">
  Go to Dashboard
</Link>
```

❌ **Disabled Button Without Explanation**
```tsx
// WRONG: User doesn't know why it's disabled
<Button variant="primary" disabled>
  Submit
</Button>

// CORRECT: Show tooltip or helper text
<Tooltip content="Complete all required fields to continue">
  <Button variant="primary" disabled>
    Submit
  </Button>
</Tooltip>
```

❌ **Primary Button Hidden Below Fold**
```tsx
// WRONG: Most important action not visible
<div className="h-screen overflow-auto">
  {/* Long content */}
  <Button variant="primary">Submit</Button>
</div>

// CORRECT: Sticky footer with primary button
<div>
  {/* Long content */}
  <div className="sticky bottom-0 bg-white p-4 border-t">
    <Button variant="primary">Submit</Button>
  </div>
</div>
```

---

### 9.12 Related Components

- **Link**: For pure navigation without actions
- **IconButton**: Specialized icon-only button variant
- **FloatingActionButton**: Fixed-position primary action
- **DropdownButton**: Button that opens a menu
- **SplitButton**: Button with dropdown menu attached

